week1
How to Run - TalentLens-AI Week 1 setup guide.

1) Create and activate a Python virtual environment.
   - python -m venv .venv
   - Linux/macOS: source .venv/bin/activate
   - Windows (cmd): .venv\Scripts\activate
   - Windows (PowerShell): .venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
2) Install project dependencies.
   - pip install -r requirements.txt
3) Install and start Ollama.
   - Install from https://ollama.com/download
   - ollama serve
   - ollama pull llama3
4) Configure Kaggle access.
   - export KAGGLE_USERNAME=your_username
   - export KAGGLE_KEY=your_key
   - or place kaggle.json in ~/.kaggle/
   - Update data/kaggle_datasets.json with Kaggle slugs in the form owner/dataset-name
   - example: kaggle.com/owner/dataset-name -> owner/dataset-name
5) Download and normalize datasets.
   - python -m talentlens.data.kaggle
   - python -m talentlens.data.normalize
   - python -m talentlens.data.policies
6) Build the resume-only index.
   - python -m talentlens.rag.index
7) Run the API server.
   - uvicorn main:app --reload
8) Optional runtime environment variables.
   - LLM_PROVIDER (default: ollama) supports: ollama, mock, none
   - OLLAMA_BASE_URL (default: http://localhost:11434)
   - OLLAMA_MODEL (default: llama3)
   - LLM_MODEL is a legacy fallback if OLLAMA_MODEL is not set
   - EMBEDDING_BACKEND=hash can be used for lightweight local runs
9) API usage flow.
   - First call /upload_resume and capture the returned resume_id
   - Then call /chat using that exact resume_id
   - If resume_id does not exist, /chat returns 404 with a clear message
